<paragraph blockId="45.[144,759,750,986]" pageId="45" pageNumber="529">
<emphasis box="[144,270,750,771]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="529">Comments:</emphasis>
This new combination is proposed based on the study of the original description and illustrations. The shape of the male genitalia in this species is similar to the members of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Matsumura" authorityYear="1931" box="[498,628,842,863]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Nippoptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,628,842,863]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="529">Nippoptilia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Yano" authorityYear="1961" box="[144,356,872,893]" class="Insecta" family="Pterophoridae" genus="Nippoptilia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="45" pageNumber="529" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="issikii">
<emphasis box="[144,356,872,893]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="529">Nippoptilia issikii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover these two species are fairly close to each other in the wing pattern and characteristics, and the host plants of both species belong to the genus 
<emphasis box="[383,443,965,986]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="529">Vittis</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
